  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Atomic Brownies</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Cookie</cat></categories>
      <yield>16</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing-div>
        <title/>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Sticks margarine</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>4</qty>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Squares unsweetened chocolate</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Sugar</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
          <item>Vanilla</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>4</qty>
            <unit/></amt>
          <item>Eggs; lightly beaten</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>cup</unit></amt>
          <item>Plus</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
          <item>Flour</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1 1/2</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Chopped nuts</item></ing></ing-div>
      <ing-div>
        <title>ICING</title>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/4</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Margarine</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>4</qty>
            <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
          <item>Evaporated milk</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Powdered sugar</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/3</qty>
            <unit>cups</unit></amt>
          <item>Cocoa</item></ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
          <item>Vanilla</item></ing></ing-div></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  From: alchazal@msuvx1.memphis.edu
  
  Date: 8 Apr 1994 23:04:22 -0400
  This is a quick recipe for brownies (or Mississippi Mud Cake in some parts
  of the country). My cousin once called this "Atomic Brownies" (biochem
  major at Columbia) because they were so dense with chocolate !
  
  Melt 2 sticks margarine with 4 squares of unsweetened chocolate. Add 2 cups
  of sugar and 2 tsps. vanilla.  Let cool slightly. Add 4 eggs, lightly
  beaten. Then add 1 c. plus 2 tlbs. flour. Add 1 1/2 c. chopped nuts. Spread
  in 13x9x2 baking dish and bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes. Cover with the
  following icing: 1/4 c. margarine heated with 4 tlbs. evaporated milk. Add
  2 c. powdered sugar, 1/3 c. cocoa, and 1 tsp. vanilla. Spread on brownies
  and cut in squares when cold (important). Enjoy !!
  
